{
  "schema_version": "wave18h.ablation_pairs.v1",
  "notes": [
    "Machine-readable corpus of PUBLISHED paired ablations (same data, same",
    "scale, one architecture axis flipped). Each pair constrains one quality",
    "residual term. observed_delta_pct is (loss_b - loss_a) / loss_a * 100;",
    "positive means arm_b is worse. Where papers report task deltas instead",
    "of loss, the loss-equivalent uses the ~1.75 pts-per-1%-loss slope from",
    "Waleffe et al.'s paired loss+task tables (noted per entry). Tolerances",
    "reflect cross-paper reporting variance, not measurement noise.",
    "This corpus is CURATION, not compute: it upgrades hand-tuned residual",
    "constants into a reproducible fit with per-term coverage auditing.",
    "vocab_residual and precision_residual currently have no published pairs; add lab pairs to constrain them."
  ],
  "pairs": [
